WEBVTT

00:02.290 --> 00:03.370
Previously on "Manifest"...

00:03.370 --> 00:06.330
Daly:Terribly sorry, folks.
That was not on the radar.

00:06.330 --> 00:11.370
You've all been missing,
presumed dead, for 5 1/2 years.

00:11.370 --> 00:12.870
Ben!

00:12.870 --> 00:14.660
Who is she?
Lourdes.

00:14.660 --> 00:16.160
That makes sense. She always
told me how lucky I was.

00:16.160 --> 00:19.080
Saanvi: I'm not ruling
out that just maybe he
came back to be saved

00:19.080 --> 00:20.290
and I came back
to save him.

00:20.290 --> 00:22.580
Earlier today, I heard
a voice in my head.
Keep it to yourself.

00:22.580 --> 00:26.450
What do you think, the
government just sent us
home and forgot about us?

00:26.450 --> 00:27.790
It's as if the plane
never left the sky.

00:27.790 --> 00:29.910
Do I have to say out loud
that that's impossible?

00:29.910 --> 00:33.000
Why you and me? What makes two
head cases like us so special?

00:33.000 --> 00:35.620
What's the probability
it's just you and me?

00:35.620 --> 00:37.870
♪♪

00:37.870 --> 00:41.080
[ Helicopter blades whirring,
siren wailing ]

00:41.080 --> 00:43.580
Cable News Reporter:
Just four days

00:43.580 --> 00:46.200
after its bewildering
reappearance,

00:46.200 --> 00:48.120
Montego Air Flight 828
is no more.

00:48.120 --> 00:51.660
British News Reporter:
Thankfully, no one was
injured in the incident.

00:51.660 --> 00:54.000
The aeroplane,
which first mystified the world

00:54.000 --> 00:55.370
after it disappeared
in April 2013...

00:55.370 --> 00:58.000
Network News Reporter: The plane
exploded shortly after midnight

00:58.000 --> 01:01.290
here on the tarmac
at Stewart Airport.

01:01.290 --> 01:02.000
Cause unknown.

01:02.000 --> 01:03.830
Sources close
to the investigation

01:03.830 --> 01:06.080
say a group
of the plane's passengers

01:06.080 --> 01:07.950
were spotted
on surveillance camera.

01:07.950 --> 01:09.660
There's more hot spots.
Can you see them?

01:09.660 --> 01:12.580
Yes, sir.
Knock those down.

01:12.580 --> 01:15.080
♪♪

01:15.080 --> 01:18.540
[ Jamaican accent ]
You don't understand.
My son is in jail.

01:18.540 --> 01:20.620
I've been trying to find him
for three days.

01:20.620 --> 01:23.450
They say I have to call him now,
this minute.

01:23.450 --> 01:25.910
He doesn't even know
I'm alive.

01:25.910 --> 01:27.910
Powell: 17.

01:31.580 --> 01:33.080
What'd you tell him?

01:33.080 --> 01:35.080
That I don't
know anything.

01:35.080 --> 01:36.000
Good. You don't.

01:36.000 --> 01:37.330
We want to stay
far off their radar.

01:37.330 --> 01:39.750
But aren't you
seeing things,

01:39.750 --> 01:42.830
hearing things
in your head?

01:42.830 --> 01:48.040
They think it's my fault.
They always blame the pilot.

01:48.040 --> 01:49.910
Look, pal.
I don't know how else to say it.

01:49.910 --> 01:55.160
I had an urge to see the plane,
I showed up, kaboom.

01:55.160 --> 01:58.750
How exactly did 20 people
have the same...urge?

01:58.750 --> 02:02.290
I sell sporting goods.
The hell you asking me for?

02:02.290 --> 02:05.410
Hi. I'm Saanvi Bahl.
You're Cal's family?
Ben Stone.

02:05.410 --> 02:08.660
This is my sister, Michaela.
How do you know Cal?

02:08.660 --> 02:10.540
I'm a doctor.
I do cancer research.

02:10.540 --> 02:12.450
Cal's new treatment
came from work I was doing

02:12.450 --> 02:14.330
before
the plane disappeared.

02:14.330 --> 02:15.290
You were on the flight?

02:15.290 --> 02:16.750
I know.
It's some coincidence --

02:16.750 --> 02:18.830
if any of this
can be a coincidence.

02:18.830 --> 02:19.500
Powell: 18.

02:19.500 --> 02:21.540
Sir, what is our status here?
Are we under arrest?

02:21.540 --> 02:23.500
No,
you're merely detained.

02:23.500 --> 02:25.080
Actually, we're not.

02:25.080 --> 02:27.160
I'm NYPD.
I know how this works.

02:27.160 --> 02:28.450
We've told you
everything that we know,

02:28.450 --> 02:32.200
so if we're not under arrest,
then you need to let us go.

02:34.080 --> 02:38.250
And radar signal
established.

02:38.250 --> 02:39.370
Ladies and gentlemen,

02:39.370 --> 02:41.540
if you've given your statements,
you're free to go.

02:41.540 --> 02:44.040
However, the events
surrounding Flight 828

02:44.040 --> 02:46.540
are a matter
of national security.

02:46.540 --> 02:49.580
You're instructed to observe
a strict media blackout.

02:49.580 --> 02:51.540
Discuss this matter
with no one.

02:51.540 --> 02:56.200
Not reporters,
not your families -- no one.

02:56.200 --> 02:59.000
You could've played the cop card
eight hours ago.

02:59.000 --> 03:01.790
Oh, you're --
you're welcome.

03:01.790 --> 03:04.250
I want eyes
on all of them.

03:04.250 --> 03:06.830
♪♪

03:06.830 --> 03:10.080
[ Engines roaring ]

03:10.080 --> 03:13.620
♪♪

03:13.620 --> 03:14.830
[ Helicopter blades whirring ]

03:14.830 --> 03:16.000
Drop me
at the precinct?

03:16.000 --> 03:17.540
Yeah, after we
swing by the house.

03:17.540 --> 03:18.870
Grace must be
worried to death.

03:18.870 --> 03:20.000
I'll take the train,
papa bear.

03:20.000 --> 03:22.830
Hey,
not a word to anyone.
'Cause NSA guy
said so?

03:22.830 --> 03:25.580
No, because it's safer that way.
We're obviously scapegoats here.

03:25.580 --> 03:28.500
And until we figure out
what happened to us,
I don't trust anyone.

03:28.500 --> 03:30.500
-What did it feel like?
-Sir, sir.

03:30.500 --> 03:32.410
You were on that plane.
-My friend. My friend.

03:32.410 --> 03:34.200
My friend, are you also police
like the woman?

03:34.200 --> 03:36.080
Uh, uh, no.
Perhaps
you can help anyway.

03:36.080 --> 03:37.750
What can you tell us
about what happened?

03:37.750 --> 03:40.620
Sir, please, please. Please.
Help me.

03:40.620 --> 03:41.750
Please, sir,
I need your help.

03:41.750 --> 03:44.660
-I'm sorry.
-Do you have any comment so far?

03:53.080 --> 03:54.370
[ Gasps ]

03:54.370 --> 03:56.950
Just me.

03:56.950 --> 03:57.660
What happened?

03:57.660 --> 03:59.750
You were at the airport
when the plane exploded?

03:59.750 --> 04:03.790
We went back to get our luggage.
It was a big misunderstanding.

04:03.790 --> 04:05.660
We're okay.

04:05.870 --> 04:07.080
Sorry.
I'm sorry.

04:07.080 --> 04:09.120
I -- I'm a little
self-conscious.

04:09.120 --> 04:11.410
We were supposed to grow old
and flabby together.

04:11.410 --> 04:14.330
Well, for the record,
you look amazing.

04:14.330 --> 04:15.160
[ Chuckles ]

04:15.160 --> 04:17.910
Brought your favorite.
[ Gasps ]

04:17.910 --> 04:20.330
Orlando's.

04:20.330 --> 04:22.080
[ Chuckles ]

04:22.080 --> 04:23.250
My God.

04:23.250 --> 04:24.750
That smell.

04:24.750 --> 04:27.370
I had
completely forgotten.

04:28.160 --> 04:29.870
Well, I kind of
dropped the ball

04:29.870 --> 04:31.580
on my weekly
blueberry-scone run.

04:31.580 --> 04:36.290
By my calculation,
I owe you 291 of these,

04:36.290 --> 04:37.830
give or take.
[ Chuckles ]

04:37.830 --> 04:40.620
Thank you.

04:40.620 --> 04:44.120
Cal: I can't find
my toothbrush.

04:44.120 --> 04:44.750
Uh, hey, bud.

04:44.750 --> 04:46.330
Mine had Batman on it.
You know what?

04:46.330 --> 04:48.750
I got you a whole pack
of cool ones.

04:48.750 --> 04:49.870
Come on.

04:49.870 --> 04:52.410
Reporter:Religious leaders
and scientists alike

04:52.410 --> 04:56.160
grapple with the mystery
of Montego Air Flight 828.

04:56.160 --> 04:56.910
Coffee? Really?

04:56.910 --> 04:59.080
So that's what
16-year-olds are doing.

04:59.080 --> 05:00.910
It's mostly
milk and sugar.

05:00.910 --> 05:02.330
Hey, so,
I've been thinking.

05:02.330 --> 05:04.450
Maybe after school,
we could hang out a bit,

05:04.450 --> 05:05.290
you know, catch up.

05:05.290 --> 05:08.750
I want to hear about,
you know, everything.

05:08.750 --> 05:09.500
I have practice,

05:09.500 --> 05:13.200
and I fell pretty behind
in my homework last week.

05:13.200 --> 05:14.500
Maybe tomorrow.

05:14.500 --> 05:16.290
Great. Whenever.

05:16.290 --> 05:22.160
[Eerie music plays]

05:22.160 --> 05:24.040
What is that?

05:24.040 --> 05:25.120
What?

05:25.120 --> 05:26.370
That music.

05:26.370 --> 05:28.870
You don't --
You don't hear that?

05:28.870 --> 05:32.330
Maybe Alexa acting up
in the den.

05:32.330 --> 05:33.250
Who's Alexa?

05:33.250 --> 05:36.750
Sweetie, it fits.
It's just a narrower cut.

05:36.750 --> 05:37.870
I think you look cool.

05:37.870 --> 05:40.120
After treatment,
we'll go shopping, okay?

05:40.120 --> 05:41.580
I just feel weird
in this.

05:41.580 --> 05:43.790
Come on. Let's see if
we can go drum up something

05:43.790 --> 05:47.000
a little less
weird-feeling.

05:49.410 --> 05:52.540
Did you
tell him yet?

05:52.540 --> 05:54.450
I will. Soon.

05:54.450 --> 05:56.410
Mom, this isn't cool.

05:56.410 --> 05:58.500
He deserves to know.

05:58.500 --> 06:05.120
♪♪

06:05.120 --> 06:10.450
[ Telephones ringing,
police radio chatter ]

06:17.700 --> 06:19.830
I came by the house
last night.

06:19.830 --> 06:22.330
Grace said
you'd gone out.

06:22.330 --> 06:24.580
♪♪

06:24.580 --> 06:27.750
Hi.

06:27.750 --> 06:29.500
♪♪

06:29.500 --> 06:31.750
Sorry, uh, Lourdes.
Hey.

06:31.750 --> 06:34.000
Um, I got to catch up
with the boss.

06:34.000 --> 06:35.830
I'll -- I'll see you soon,
okay?

06:35.830 --> 06:45.580
♪♪

06:45.580 --> 06:48.370
[ Knock on door ]
Michaela:
Hey, Captain.

06:49.700 --> 06:52.540
What happened to, uh,
taking some time for yourself?

06:52.540 --> 06:55.950
I can either sit at home
staring at my ceiling

06:55.950 --> 06:58.500
or I can
get back to work.

06:58.500 --> 07:00.120
[ Chuckles ]

07:00.120 --> 07:02.370
So,
here's how it is.

07:02.370 --> 07:03.950
I want this
to happen --

07:03.950 --> 07:05.620
you've got that
going for ya --

07:05.620 --> 07:09.120
but I can't sign off until
you jump through the hoops --

07:09.120 --> 07:13.410
the physical,
firearms re-cert, psych eval.

07:13.410 --> 07:15.620
Since when is a psych eval
a hoop?

07:15.620 --> 07:17.790
We're in
uncharted waters here.

07:17.790 --> 07:20.790
After all
you've been through...

07:22.620 --> 07:25.830
Is that all?
That's all.

07:27.370 --> 07:30.160
[ Tablet chimes ]

07:30.160 --> 07:33.450
Reporter:A hollow shell
is all that remains

07:33.450 --> 07:35.410
of Montego Air Flight 828.

07:35.410 --> 07:37.080
While multiple
government agencies

07:37.080 --> 07:39.250
survey the wreckage
and look for clues...

07:39.250 --> 07:41.000
Do you have
any different-colored pens?

07:41.000 --> 07:43.870
Uh, no, but we can get you
a whole bunch at the store --

07:43.870 --> 07:45.700
sketchpad like you had,
the works.

07:45.700 --> 07:48.160
Okay.
[ Cellphone rings, clicks ]

07:49.660 --> 07:50.290
Hey, guys.

07:50.290 --> 07:52.620
Honey, this is,
uh, the doctor I told you about.

07:52.620 --> 07:54.200
Nice to meet you.
Oh, hi, there.

07:54.200 --> 07:58.160
You all being on the plane
together, it's miraculous.

07:58.160 --> 07:59.290
Yeah,
so my parents say.

07:59.290 --> 08:00.750
They've been praying
at every meal.

08:00.750 --> 08:03.450
But right now, I'm gonna focus
my energy on this guy.

08:03.450 --> 08:05.370
You ready
for round two, buddy?
Yep.

08:05.370 --> 08:07.450
See you, bud.
Get 'em.

08:07.450 --> 08:10.160
Saanvi:
Later, Mom and Dad.

08:10.160 --> 08:12.950
[ Cellphone rings, clicks ]

08:12.950 --> 08:15.330
Need to take that?

08:15.330 --> 08:16.700
No,
it's just a work thing.

08:16.700 --> 08:17.830
I'm catering
this office party,

08:17.830 --> 08:19.620
and the client's
always checking in.
[ Sighs ]

08:19.620 --> 08:21.330
Of course.
I keep forgetting.

08:21.330 --> 08:23.000
My wife,
the entrepreneur.

08:23.000 --> 08:26.000
Ah, well.
[ Chuckles ]

08:26.000 --> 08:28.160
Look, you must have
a ton to take care of,

08:28.160 --> 08:29.790
so why don't I
take a walk?
No, no, no.

08:29.790 --> 08:31.700
You don't --
I can make
some job-search calls,

08:31.700 --> 08:33.200
and we can meet
later back home.

08:33.200 --> 08:35.200
I'll take
tomorrow's shift.

08:35.200 --> 08:37.370
I'll call you later.

08:37.370 --> 08:43.620
♪♪

08:43.620 --> 08:46.040
[ Horn blares ]

08:46.040 --> 08:48.120
[ Indistinct conversations ]

08:48.120 --> 08:52.120
[ Siren wails in distance ]

08:56.160 --> 09:02.200
[Eerie music plays]

09:02.200 --> 09:05.790
Do you hear that?
Hear what?

09:08.450 --> 09:12.620
[Music continues]

09:12.620 --> 09:22.200
♪♪

09:22.200 --> 09:25.080
[Music continues]

09:25.080 --> 09:31.700
[ Violin playing ]

09:33.080 --> 09:38.120
♪♪

09:38.120 --> 09:39.660
Ben: You.

09:39.660 --> 09:40.910
That melody.

09:40.910 --> 09:44.450
That's been clanging in my head
all day.

09:44.450 --> 09:47.660
I need help.
Please.

09:47.660 --> 09:50.200
Please.

09:51.450 --> 09:53.870
[ Siren wails in distance ]

09:55.870 --> 09:58.540
First it was the plane,
the vision.

09:58.540 --> 10:02.790
Then this morning, the music
beating against my eardrums.

10:02.790 --> 10:06.660
No voices?
You are hearing voices?

10:06.790 --> 10:10.580
Eh, I'm not sure
what I'm hearing -- or why.

10:10.580 --> 10:13.000
For me,
music is a higher power.

10:13.000 --> 10:16.040
So this music we hear,
you and I together,

10:16.040 --> 10:16.830
it's for a reason.

10:16.830 --> 10:20.120
And that reason
has to be my son.

10:20.120 --> 10:21.200
He's the one
who needs help.

10:21.200 --> 10:25.250
I was with you in Jamaica
to play with the philharmonic.

10:25.250 --> 10:25.870
One night.

10:25.870 --> 10:28.950
But I left a 13-year-old child
with my neighbor,

10:28.950 --> 10:32.200
and I returned
to an 18-year-old man --

10:32.200 --> 10:35.160
a man that is now
behind bars.

10:35.160 --> 10:37.000
Ah, I'm sorry.

10:37.000 --> 10:39.000
[ Sighs ]
What happened?

10:39.000 --> 10:40.120
Police say
it was robbery.

10:40.120 --> 10:42.870
But that's impossible, you know,
'cause Adio's a good boy.

10:42.870 --> 10:44.950
If I could just
talk to him,

10:44.950 --> 10:46.750
there'd be an explanation,
I know this.

10:46.750 --> 10:48.250
Sounds like
you need a lawyer.

10:48.250 --> 10:49.540
Ineedto see my son.

10:49.540 --> 10:51.200
The jail said
I need to be on a list,

10:51.200 --> 10:54.200
but I'm a resident alien
and my visa's expired.

10:54.200 --> 10:55.410
They say
it could take a month,

10:55.410 --> 10:57.580
but Adio don't have that long,
you know?

10:57.580 --> 10:59.290
His trial's next week.

10:59.290 --> 11:01.000
Please, please.

11:01.000 --> 11:02.450
You know the police.

11:02.450 --> 11:04.200
You're a father, yes?

11:04.200 --> 11:04.950
Boy and a girl.

11:04.950 --> 11:07.040
Adio's already been five years
without a father.

11:07.040 --> 11:12.660
Can you imagine not being able
to save your own child?

11:14.080 --> 11:15.700
I've been through
your file.

11:15.700 --> 11:17.500
Seems like your world
turned upside down

11:17.500 --> 11:21.250
five monthsbefore you got on that plane.

11:22.750 --> 11:26.290
My friend died.
We had a car accident.

11:26.290 --> 11:28.700
You were the driver
and you'd been drinking?

11:28.700 --> 11:30.040
That would weigh heavily
on anyone.

11:30.040 --> 11:32.200
Well, there was an
investigation, and
I was exonerated.

11:32.200 --> 11:35.040
But still
put on desk duty.
Yeah,
I couldn't drive.

11:35.040 --> 11:37.410
I wasn't ready.
I didn't want to.

11:37.410 --> 11:40.450
Sorry. What -- What exactly
is the point here?

11:40.450 --> 11:42.500
I'm trying
to help you process

11:42.500 --> 11:44.290
the magnitude of changes
in your life

11:44.290 --> 11:47.080
in the last five years.
Last four days.

11:47.080 --> 11:48.410
That's my point --

11:48.410 --> 11:51.910
to absorb so much change
in so little time.

11:51.910 --> 11:53.250
You don't have to hide
your emotions.

11:53.250 --> 11:56.200
I'm on your side.
Due respect,
but you're not.

11:56.200 --> 11:57.450
Look,
I know the drill here.

11:57.450 --> 12:00.330
I break down
and you mark me unfit for duty,

12:00.330 --> 12:01.160
but I am okay.

12:01.160 --> 12:02.410
So how about
letting me get back

12:02.410 --> 12:08.120
to the one thing
that I do have left -- my job?

12:12.450 --> 12:14.500
[ Inhales deeply ]
[ Pen scribbles ]

12:14.500 --> 12:17.700
I'll need
to see you again.

12:19.290 --> 12:22.580
[ Cellphone rings, beeps ]
Hey.

12:22.580 --> 12:23.750
You okay?

12:23.750 --> 12:25.830
Yeah, bureaucracy.
What's up?

12:25.830 --> 12:27.250
I need a favor.

12:27.250 --> 12:29.200
Know anyone at Rikers?

12:29.200 --> 12:31.250
Man:
15 minutes, break's over!

12:31.250 --> 12:34.160
[ Door buzzes ]

12:37.910 --> 12:40.330
♪♪

12:40.330 --> 12:42.660
[ Door closes ]

12:42.660 --> 13:03.370
♪♪

13:03.370 --> 13:05.410
[ Exhales deeply ]

13:05.410 --> 13:07.330
I didn't believe it.

13:07.330 --> 13:10.620
Then I saw
your face on TV.

13:11.910 --> 13:13.660
Where were you?

13:13.660 --> 13:16.790
I wish I knew.

13:18.790 --> 13:20.910
Who did this to you?

13:20.910 --> 13:23.370
Doesn't matter.

13:23.370 --> 13:26.950
Whatever they told you,
I didn't do it.

13:26.950 --> 13:29.290
Of course you didn't.

13:32.250 --> 13:33.580
[ Grunts ]

13:33.580 --> 13:38.500
You always said
you have to be a good man.

13:38.500 --> 13:39.330
I tried. I have.

13:39.330 --> 13:41.700
School, no banging --
all that.

13:41.700 --> 13:45.160
I got a job at a jewelry store
on 47th Street.

13:45.160 --> 13:46.580
Sometimes,
I would close up.

13:46.580 --> 13:49.950
One night a month ago,
I got jumped in the back room,

13:49.950 --> 13:53.040
and when I came to,
everything was gone,

13:53.040 --> 13:55.160
and they think
that I was a part of it.

13:55.160 --> 13:58.080
Adio,
what happened to your face

13:58.080 --> 14:01.250
is not
from a month ago.

14:01.250 --> 14:04.000
Hmm?

14:06.000 --> 14:17.410
♪♪

14:17.410 --> 14:20.870
[ Voice breaking ] I'm going
to fight for you, son.

14:20.870 --> 14:22.120
♪♪

14:22.120 --> 14:25.250
[ Quietly ]
I'm going to fight for you.

14:25.250 --> 14:28.830
♪♪

14:28.830 --> 14:31.830
[ Horn honks ]

14:31.830 --> 14:35.200
Just up here.

14:35.370 --> 14:39.370
It's the exact set you had.
It's just a different box.

14:39.370 --> 14:42.250
It's not.
Mine had superhero minifigs.

14:42.250 --> 14:43.040
This one doesn't.

14:43.040 --> 14:45.410
Okay, we'll look at it
when we get home, all right?

14:45.410 --> 14:50.580
Besides, you know, you can
mix three sets together, right?

14:50.580 --> 14:51.910
He is risen.

14:51.910 --> 14:53.950
He is not here.

14:53.950 --> 14:56.200
He is risen.
Let go of him.

14:56.200 --> 14:57.660
He is risen.

14:57.660 --> 14:59.450
He is not here.

14:59.450 --> 15:00.830
He is risen.

15:00.830 --> 15:04.540
♪♪

15:04.540 --> 15:06.450
[ Bell dings ]

15:06.450 --> 15:10.370
Everything left's
in the, uh, far case.

15:10.370 --> 15:12.160
Actually,
we're here about Adio.

15:12.160 --> 15:13.750
We still doing this?

15:13.750 --> 15:15.910
What happened
to the last detectives?

15:15.910 --> 15:20.500
Uh, we're not the police.
This is Adio's father.

15:20.500 --> 15:23.410
You got some nerve
walking in here.

15:23.410 --> 15:26.290
He cleaned me out --
entire inventory.

15:26.290 --> 15:28.450
41 years up in smoke.

15:28.450 --> 15:30.540
Some son you raised.

15:30.540 --> 15:31.250
You...

15:31.250 --> 15:34.540
Sorry.
My dad's actually a good guy.

15:34.540 --> 15:35.370
And so is my son.

15:35.370 --> 15:36.620
Look,
I don't know what to think.

15:36.620 --> 15:39.120
I mean, we didn't even know
Adio was his name

15:39.120 --> 15:40.040
until the cops said so.

15:40.040 --> 15:42.000
Turned out,
he gave us a fake I.D.,

15:42.000 --> 15:43.040
fake job references.

15:43.040 --> 15:46.750
So when everything disappears,
no tripped alarm,

15:46.750 --> 15:49.040
he's the only one here?

15:49.660 --> 15:50.950
Ben: Tell me
exactly what she said.

15:50.950 --> 15:52.160
I wasn't focusing
on the words.

15:52.160 --> 15:55.160
I don't remember.
I -- Just it was scary.

15:55.160 --> 15:55.870
But he's fine?

15:55.870 --> 15:58.750
As fine as can be expected
after chemo

15:58.750 --> 16:00.290
and a crazy lady
praying in your face.

16:00.290 --> 16:02.950
We will get past this soon
enough. I'm gonna figure it out.

16:02.950 --> 16:04.120
I love
your problem-solving mind,

16:04.120 --> 16:07.410
but I need to know
that Cal is going to be safe.

16:07.410 --> 16:08.200
This'll die down.

16:08.200 --> 16:10.500
We just need to be
extra vigilant until it does.

16:10.500 --> 16:13.290
And what if it doesn't?
You've seen the news.

16:13.290 --> 16:15.950
The whole world
is obsessing over us.

16:15.950 --> 16:18.910
People can go online
and find out where we live.

16:18.910 --> 16:20.790
We will be okay.

16:20.790 --> 16:22.290
I mean, come on.

16:22.290 --> 16:25.750
We got a cop
that lives in our house.

16:28.410 --> 16:30.040
Trigger finger
still works.

16:30.040 --> 16:31.410
Yeah,
what do you expect?

16:31.410 --> 16:34.290
I had range time
10 days ago...

16:34.290 --> 16:35.450
my time.

16:35.450 --> 16:38.870
About this morning...

16:38.870 --> 16:39.580
Lourdes --

16:39.580 --> 16:42.040
I didn't mean to --
[ Both sigh ]

16:42.040 --> 16:44.910
I just need time,
okay?

16:44.910 --> 16:47.120
Mick, if you held this
against me for the rest of my --

16:47.120 --> 16:49.660
I told you I don't hold anything
against you.

16:49.660 --> 16:53.200
Well, you could,
and I'd -- I'd get it.

16:53.200 --> 16:55.950
And please
don't punish Lourdes.

16:55.950 --> 16:59.080
I'm not punishing her,
Jared,

16:59.080 --> 17:00.950
but I saw her and you,

17:00.950 --> 17:05.830
and I felt like puking
or fainting or both.

17:05.830 --> 17:08.250
If you could just put yourself
in her shoes --
Really?

17:08.250 --> 17:10.000
Is that
where you're gonna go?

17:10.000 --> 17:13.160
Losing Evie was hard enough,
but then you?

17:13.160 --> 17:17.750
Lourdes lost her best friend
when you disappeared.

17:17.750 --> 17:20.450
She never replaced you.

17:20.450 --> 17:23.410
♪♪

17:23.410 --> 17:26.290
And I couldn't
replace you.

17:26.290 --> 17:32.120
♪♪

17:32.120 --> 17:33.290
[ Sighs ]

17:33.290 --> 17:35.200
Now, at this point,
we have no evidence

17:35.200 --> 17:37.540
of passenger or crew involvement
in the explosion.

17:37.540 --> 17:41.450
But that said, we continue
to suspect some nexus between --

17:41.450 --> 17:43.040
Willick: Director Vance,
if I may.

17:43.040 --> 17:45.040
The explosion is a bit
beside the point.

17:45.040 --> 17:48.040
Where did that plane go
for 5 1/2 years?

17:48.040 --> 17:49.000
Theories abound.

17:49.000 --> 17:50.910
We could be talking about
a wormhole,

17:50.910 --> 17:53.620
about some kind of
extraterrestrial encounter.

17:53.620 --> 17:55.830
But more to the point,
are we in danger?

17:55.830 --> 17:58.540
Was the plane targeted
by some kind of weapon?

17:58.540 --> 17:59.910
Or isitthe weapon?

17:59.910 --> 18:01.620
Do we even know
if those are the same people

18:01.620 --> 18:03.620
that were on that plane
in 2013?

18:03.620 --> 18:05.790
We've tested comprehensive
samples of the passengers

18:05.790 --> 18:07.000
and haven't detected
any anomalies.

18:07.000 --> 18:09.160
This is national security
we're talking about.

18:09.160 --> 18:10.160
They should be incarcerated

18:10.160 --> 18:11.790
until we can determine
whether or not they're a threat.

18:11.790 --> 18:15.290
Director Hughes, this
is still America. These
people have rights.

18:15.290 --> 18:18.080
I-I suspect
if anyone has answers,

18:18.080 --> 18:19.200
it's someone on that plane,

18:19.200 --> 18:22.410
most likely someone we found
standing 100 yards away

18:22.410 --> 18:27.080
when it blew to bits,
which leaves 20 people.

18:27.080 --> 18:32.700
♪♪

18:33.040 --> 18:34.700
[ Door closes ]Of course we were confused.

18:36.200 --> 18:37.040
What, you cook now?

18:37.040 --> 18:39.450
Just when I thought things
couldn't get any stranger.

18:39.450 --> 18:41.200
Hey,
thanks for the jail hookup.

18:41.200 --> 18:42.410
How is Radd's son?

18:42.410 --> 18:43.950
His face
is bashed in.

18:43.950 --> 18:44.950
It's not safe
in there.

18:44.950 --> 18:46.700
Yeah, well, if he gets convicted
and goes upstate,

18:46.700 --> 18:48.950
the place he's at now is
gonna seem like a country club.

18:49.950 --> 18:54.250
I so want this kid to be
innocent for his father's sake.

18:54.250 --> 18:55.700
Hey,
can you pull the file

18:55.700 --> 18:57.620
and see if the cops or D.A.
cut some corners?

18:57.620 --> 18:59.250
So it's the --
the police's fault?

18:59.250 --> 19:01.540
I'm just
spit-balling here.

19:01.540 --> 19:02.950
Doesn't seem fair that
that flight

19:02.950 --> 19:06.660
may have saved my kid's life
but threatened someone else's.

19:08.450 --> 19:11.870
You heard something
like last time.

19:12.200 --> 19:14.160
[ Bowl thuds ]
Not exactly.

19:14.160 --> 19:16.250
But whatever that was,
whatever this is,

19:16.250 --> 19:17.500
I've got to get
to the bottom of it.

19:17.500 --> 19:19.330
No, Ben, not everything is
a puzzle that you have to solve.

19:19.330 --> 19:20.580
It isn't about
solving a puzzle.

19:20.580 --> 19:24.790
This is understanding what
my life has become --ourlives.

19:24.790 --> 19:27.750
♪♪

19:27.750 --> 19:29.410
If we can't answer that,

19:29.410 --> 19:33.330
we're never gonna be able
to get back to normal.

19:35.870 --> 19:37.450
Have you told Grace?

19:37.450 --> 19:38.370
No.

19:38.370 --> 19:41.120
She has enough going on.

19:41.120 --> 19:45.450
♪♪

19:46.330 --> 19:48.540
These aren't the same.

19:48.540 --> 19:50.910
[ Sighs ] Really?

19:52.000 --> 19:54.700
Well, we can try
another store tomorrow.

19:54.700 --> 19:58.580
All right, dinner's ready.
Olive!

19:58.580 --> 20:01.410
Up high.

20:01.410 --> 20:03.410
It smells incredible.

20:05.910 --> 20:07.830
Hey,
how about after dinner,

20:07.830 --> 20:10.330
we go for
an old-school ice-cream run?

20:10.330 --> 20:11.330
[ Chuckles ]

20:11.330 --> 20:12.910
You still like
ice cream, right?

20:12.910 --> 20:16.120
I've got to study.
[ Chuckles ]

20:16.120 --> 20:17.790
Soon.

20:18.750 --> 20:21.200
[ Sighs ]

20:21.700 --> 20:25.290
[ Insects chirping ]

20:26.410 --> 20:28.830
[ Sighs ]

20:30.330 --> 20:34.330
[ Ticking ]

20:34.330 --> 20:43.500
♪♪

20:43.500 --> 20:46.450
[ Children laughing ]

20:46.450 --> 20:49.000
♪♪

20:49.000 --> 20:50.620
Ah!

20:50.620 --> 20:51.750
Ah, come here.

20:51.750 --> 20:53.370
Come here.
[ Laughter ]

20:53.370 --> 20:56.950
You are supposed to be
in bed!
Come here.

20:56.950 --> 20:59.200
Grr!

20:59.200 --> 21:00.580
Rawr!

21:00.580 --> 21:04.540
♪♪

21:04.540 --> 21:08.120
My God, we're the parents
of a teenage girl.

21:08.120 --> 21:10.910
Be thankful
you missed puberty.

21:10.910 --> 21:12.830
[ Chuckles ]

21:17.250 --> 21:18.250
Ouch.

21:18.250 --> 21:19.790
How'd that happen?

21:19.790 --> 21:23.250
Oh.
Scuba diving, actually.

21:23.250 --> 21:24.290
Excuse me?

21:24.290 --> 21:26.910
How many times
did I want us to try diving?

21:26.910 --> 21:28.910
[ Chuckles ]
Well, I tried it.

21:28.910 --> 21:30.830
Turns out,
it leaves a mark.

21:30.830 --> 21:37.200
Okay, well,
you can teach me.

21:42.160 --> 21:48.370
♪♪

21:48.370 --> 21:50.870
Grace: You know
how hard this is.

21:50.870 --> 21:55.660
It hasn't even been a week.

21:55.660 --> 21:58.000
♪♪

21:58.000 --> 22:00.250
Of course I do.

22:00.250 --> 22:03.080
[ Sighs deeply ]

22:03.080 --> 22:05.750
I will.

22:05.750 --> 22:08.160
Bye.

22:08.160 --> 22:11.080
[ Cellphone beeps ]

22:15.250 --> 22:18.700
You too.

22:20.950 --> 22:23.500
Do I know him?

22:24.540 --> 22:26.750
Does Ben?

22:26.750 --> 22:27.950
No.

22:27.950 --> 22:32.000
Mick, nobody did
anything wrong here.

22:32.000 --> 22:34.870
Not me,
not Jared, not Lourdes.

22:34.870 --> 22:36.620
Not me or Ben.

22:36.620 --> 22:39.450
No, of course not.

22:39.450 --> 22:42.580
I am
going to tell him.

22:42.580 --> 22:45.410
I just...

22:46.580 --> 22:49.620
I need to figure out
what I'm gonna do.

22:49.620 --> 22:51.750
Meaning...

22:51.750 --> 22:54.200
who you're gonna be with?

22:55.620 --> 22:56.330
Wow.

22:56.330 --> 22:57.750
Grace, look,
I know that you guys

22:57.750 --> 22:59.870
didn't have a perfect marriage,
but really?

22:59.870 --> 23:01.410
He is your --
He is your husband.

23:01.410 --> 23:03.120
[ Voice breaking ]
I know.

23:03.120 --> 23:06.660
And I love him.

23:06.660 --> 23:09.790
God help me.

23:10.500 --> 23:12.830
I didn't even remember
how much I loved him

23:12.830 --> 23:13.750
until he came back.

23:13.750 --> 23:18.950
But you have to understand
this is an impossible situation.

23:18.950 --> 23:21.330
This is
none of my business,

23:21.330 --> 23:26.330
but you need to figure this out
before Ben does.

23:26.330 --> 23:29.120
He's going through enough.

23:29.120 --> 23:35.290
♪♪

23:35.290 --> 23:37.160
Kelly:They said
it was the electrolytes,

23:37.160 --> 23:38.910
but who knows
what was really in there?

23:38.910 --> 23:42.620
Reporter:Are you saying you think
the government drugged you?

23:42.620 --> 23:45.080
I'm just trying
to own my truth.

23:45.080 --> 23:47.750
I don't know for sure
what happened,

23:47.750 --> 23:49.160
but I'm beginning
to think that

23:49.160 --> 23:50.830
they didn't tell us everything
that was going on.

23:50.830 --> 23:55.120
They gave us stuff
to eat and drink from a box...

23:55.120 --> 23:57.450
I'll be right back.

23:57.450 --> 23:58.870
What's up?

23:58.870 --> 24:00.330
I, um...

24:00.330 --> 24:02.790
God,
this is gonna sound nuts.

24:02.790 --> 24:04.620
But you did come back
to the plane, too,

24:04.620 --> 24:08.000
so I'm guessing you're already
questioning your sanity.

24:08.000 --> 24:10.660
I'm questioning
a lot of things.

24:10.660 --> 24:13.750
Have you been...

24:13.750 --> 24:15.660
hearing music?

24:15.660 --> 24:19.540
You mean, like,
in my head?

24:19.660 --> 24:24.080
I haven't heard any music,
but I've had a similar feeling

24:24.080 --> 24:26.120
more than once
since we've been back.

24:26.120 --> 24:29.870
Yeah, well, at least I know
I'm not going crazy.

24:29.870 --> 24:30.540
[ Chuckles ]

24:30.540 --> 24:33.410
Or at least
you're not the only one.

24:35.540 --> 24:37.790
Hey, dude.
Family portrait?

24:37.790 --> 24:43.750
Yep. Me with no cancer,
my mom and dad, my sister.

24:43.750 --> 24:44.950
Who's that?

24:44.950 --> 24:47.200
I don't know.

24:48.330 --> 24:50.370
You ready?
Yep.

24:50.370 --> 24:52.870
All right,
let's go.

24:54.290 --> 24:56.450
[ Sighs ]

24:57.950 --> 25:10.200
♪♪

25:10.200 --> 25:13.000
[ Alarm chirps ]

25:13.000 --> 25:16.080
♪♪

25:16.080 --> 25:19.500
[ Engine starts ]

25:28.410 --> 25:30.330
Police work checks out,
Ben.

25:30.330 --> 25:32.450
Adio was
the only one on duty.

25:32.450 --> 25:34.000
I mean,
he said he was attacked,

25:34.000 --> 25:36.370
but there's no signs
of forced entry

25:36.370 --> 25:39.330
and other than
the ding on his head...

25:39.330 --> 25:40.250
You think he's lying.

25:40.250 --> 25:41.450
No, I don't know
what to think,

25:41.450 --> 25:44.620
but the kid had 12 grand
stashed in his apartment

25:44.620 --> 25:45.410
and he's got a record.

25:45.410 --> 25:47.000
I mean --
Shoplifting,
jumping turnstiles?

25:47.000 --> 25:50.290
This is minor stuff.
Yeah, but it's what a jury
will look at and say,

25:50.290 --> 25:51.910
"That kid's
heading the wrong direction."

25:51.910 --> 25:53.330
[ Sighs ]
There has to be more I can do.

25:53.330 --> 25:56.330
I mean, why else
would I have been drawn in?
Okay, science boy.

25:56.330 --> 25:58.870
Mom was the one
who believed in miracles.

25:58.870 --> 25:59.620
Forget miracles.

25:59.620 --> 26:01.330
Every day Adio is in there,
his life is in danger.

26:01.330 --> 26:02.950
Yeah, well,
Mom would also say,

26:02.950 --> 26:04.120
"God works
in mysterious ways."

26:04.120 --> 26:06.580
You know, you can stop
goading me any time now.

26:06.580 --> 26:10.000
I'm not convinced God
has anything to do with this.

26:10.000 --> 26:11.000
You think God
wanted Jared

26:11.000 --> 26:15.000
to marry your best friend
instead of you?

26:15.370 --> 26:19.830
That was a terrible thing
to say.

26:20.330 --> 26:21.410
[ Sighs ]

26:21.410 --> 26:24.700
And yet
kind of a fair question.

26:31.290 --> 26:32.660
I'm one to talk.

26:32.660 --> 26:34.410
Olive barely looks me
in the eye,

26:34.410 --> 26:37.450
Grace is trying,
but...

26:37.450 --> 26:41.000
I still feel like a stranger
in my own home.

26:41.000 --> 26:43.500
♪♪

26:43.500 --> 26:46.870
I did what I did to get by --
fake I.D. so I can work,

26:46.870 --> 26:49.160
shoplifted so I can --
so I can eat.

26:49.160 --> 26:50.120
No, no, no, no.

26:50.120 --> 26:51.910
None of this
is your fault.

26:51.910 --> 26:54.330
I left you alone.

26:55.040 --> 26:57.830
So if
you did something,

26:57.830 --> 27:00.370
even
out of desperation --

27:00.370 --> 27:02.000
I didn't!

27:02.000 --> 27:04.790
They beat on me just like
they beating on me in here.

27:04.790 --> 27:07.200
Is there anything he could tell
us that might help confirm --

27:07.200 --> 27:09.200
Look, I did like you taught me.
I kept my head down.

27:09.200 --> 27:10.580
I worked my ass off
being a good man.

27:10.580 --> 27:12.580
One more minute.
Being a good man.
Tell them.

27:12.580 --> 27:13.830
Just tell them.
Just tell them, Dad.

27:13.830 --> 27:15.290
Please, please,tata.Tell them that I'm good.

27:15.290 --> 27:18.540
Please, sir.
Tell them, please. Wait, wait.
Please. Just tell them.

27:18.540 --> 27:19.870
Please, sir!
Give us more time!

27:19.870 --> 27:23.580
Don't do this! Just --
Just give us another minute!

27:23.580 --> 27:39.370
♪♪

27:39.370 --> 27:43.830
Happy birthday, Mick.
I miss you.

27:43.830 --> 28:10.080
♪♪

28:10.080 --> 28:13.330
[ Sniffles ]

28:13.330 --> 28:16.620
[ Crying ]

28:16.620 --> 28:21.000
♪♪

28:21.000 --> 28:24.000
Um...

28:24.000 --> 28:26.660
off-center.

28:26.660 --> 28:29.370
Pissed.

28:30.580 --> 28:32.750
Mostly sad.

28:32.750 --> 28:36.540
And why is that?

28:36.540 --> 28:39.120
Uh...

28:40.410 --> 28:42.660
...because I miss
my mom.

28:42.660 --> 28:47.410
'Cause you don't just stop
being in love with someone.

28:47.410 --> 28:49.500
Um...

28:49.500 --> 28:51.500
'cause my best friend
in the world,

28:51.500 --> 28:56.830
the person I would normally
complain to instead of you

28:56.830 --> 28:59.450
gets to love the person
that I can't.

28:59.450 --> 29:01.660
Howisthat friendship?

29:01.660 --> 29:03.000
Lourdes?

29:03.000 --> 29:09.580
She sent beautiful messages
to a ghost for...

29:09.580 --> 29:10.580
for five years,

29:10.580 --> 29:15.080
and I come back,
and I...

29:15.080 --> 29:17.330
couldn't even hug her.

29:17.330 --> 29:21.580
All of the people
that I would normally talk to --

29:21.580 --> 29:26.080
Lourdes, Evie,
my mom...

29:26.080 --> 29:29.120
You feel alone.

29:32.160 --> 29:34.040
[ Sighs ]

29:34.040 --> 29:37.950
And out comes
the disability form.

29:37.950 --> 29:38.950
Get what you wanted?

29:38.950 --> 29:41.700
You've accepted
what's happened.

29:41.700 --> 29:44.500
That's a good first step.

29:44.500 --> 29:49.750
I'm recommending your
conditional reinstatement...

29:49.750 --> 29:52.080
[ Pen scribbles ]

29:52.080 --> 29:54.830
...but I want
to keep seeing you.

29:54.830 --> 29:59.040
♪♪

29:59.040 --> 30:02.500
[ Police radio chatter ]

30:02.500 --> 30:04.910
Hey,
I heard the news.

30:04.910 --> 30:07.290
Congratulations,
Detective.

30:07.290 --> 30:09.910
Oh, yeah,
it was a posthumous promotion.

30:09.910 --> 30:10.700
I didn't earn it.

30:10.700 --> 30:12.500
I can't even die
the way I'm supposed to.

30:12.500 --> 30:14.370
Just take the win,
would you?

30:14.370 --> 30:18.120
And if anyone deserves to have
a break go in there direction...

30:18.120 --> 30:18.950
Thanks.

30:18.950 --> 30:23.290
I'll try not to make it
too awkward around here.

30:24.410 --> 30:25.540
Ben: Hey.

30:25.540 --> 30:27.950
Grace:
How was your day?
Good.

30:27.950 --> 30:30.580
Hey, check it out --
Every comfy t-shirt

30:30.580 --> 30:34.370
and cool LEGO set
on the planet Earth.

30:34.370 --> 30:36.200
Thanks, Mom.

30:36.200 --> 30:39.870
[ Chuckling ] Whoa.

30:41.040 --> 30:43.290
Is everything okay?

30:43.290 --> 30:46.160
It's fine.
Ben:
What's up, buddy?

30:46.160 --> 30:47.790
I missmystuff --

30:47.790 --> 30:50.750
my rock collection,
Art the Dragon.

30:50.750 --> 30:54.750
Oh, Cal, listen...

30:54.750 --> 30:56.700
it's okay to be sad.

30:56.700 --> 30:57.870
I get sad sometimes,
too.

30:57.870 --> 31:02.160
I just want everything
back the way it was.

31:02.160 --> 31:06.000
Aw, sweetie,
I know, I know.

31:06.000 --> 31:09.450
Dad,
can we take that ride now?

31:09.450 --> 31:10.870
After two years or so,

31:10.870 --> 31:13.370
the house
was exactly the same.

31:13.370 --> 31:16.790
It was like
this sad museum

31:16.790 --> 31:19.790
and the shrink said
we needed to let go

31:19.790 --> 31:22.700
and Mom
was a wreck and I...

31:22.700 --> 31:25.330
Honey, if you weren't a wreck
anymore after two years,

31:25.330 --> 31:27.620
I'd say
that sounded pretty healthy.

31:27.620 --> 31:28.620
Wasn't it.

31:28.620 --> 31:32.080
I knew
Cal wasn't dead.

31:32.080 --> 31:33.750
You did?

31:33.750 --> 31:36.540
I don't know if it was
some kind of twin thing,

31:36.540 --> 31:40.750
but I could --
I could feel him...alive.

31:40.750 --> 31:44.160
And the therapist,
the counselors at school, Mom,

31:44.160 --> 31:48.790
everyone blew it off,
blewmeoff, but I knew.

31:48.790 --> 31:50.160
Okay.

31:50.160 --> 31:51.870
Does this connect
to why we're in

31:51.870 --> 31:55.700
a pretty gross-smelling
storage facility on Long Island?

31:55.700 --> 31:57.410
Mom listened
to the shrink, okay?

31:57.410 --> 32:00.580
Sh-She packed all your
and Cal's stuff away in boxes,

32:00.580 --> 32:03.910
left on the curb
for Salvation Army

32:03.910 --> 32:05.540
and then
went to work.

32:05.540 --> 32:09.290
I called,
and I cancelled the pickup.

32:09.290 --> 32:11.870
Well, if you've had his stuff
all this time,

32:11.870 --> 32:14.250
why didn't you
say something?

32:14.250 --> 32:15.950
It's complicated.

32:15.950 --> 32:20.040
Mom doesn't know
about any of this.

32:29.290 --> 32:31.950
[ Sighs ]

32:34.500 --> 32:37.620
[ Sighs ]

32:38.700 --> 32:41.790
Olive,
whose locker is this?

32:44.500 --> 32:45.750
Olive.

32:45.750 --> 32:48.620
Friend of Mom's,
all right?

32:48.620 --> 32:52.080
"Friend."

32:52.080 --> 32:53.370
Dad.

32:53.370 --> 32:56.120
Okay.
Come here.

32:56.120 --> 32:58.870
You did
the right thing.

32:58.870 --> 33:00.620
[ Sighs ]

33:00.620 --> 33:03.330
[Eerie music plays]

33:03.330 --> 33:06.250
Hey, are you --
are you okay?

33:06.250 --> 33:10.540
Stay here, okay?
Stay here.

33:13.040 --> 33:16.160
[Eerie music playing]

33:16.160 --> 33:27.200
♪♪

33:27.200 --> 33:31.950
[ Cellphone ringtone
plays tune ]

33:34.660 --> 33:36.750
[ Cellphone clicks ]
Man: Hello?

33:36.750 --> 33:40.040
Y-Yeah,
meet me in the back.

33:40.040 --> 33:44.910
Yeah, uh, watches,
diamond rings, bracelets.

33:44.910 --> 33:45.750
Fine. Yeah.

33:45.750 --> 33:47.700
I'll take 10, but you got to
get this stuff out of state.

33:47.700 --> 33:51.950
People are looking for it.
Whoa. How did you --

33:51.950 --> 33:53.870
♪♪

33:53.870 --> 33:55.370
W-- It's not
what it looks like.

33:55.370 --> 33:58.330
You robbed your own father
and blamed Adio.

33:58.330 --> 33:59.910
♪♪

33:59.910 --> 34:02.790
You can take half of this.
Seriously. Come on.

34:02.790 --> 34:05.790
I mean, that kid was going
nowhere. He was just a --

34:05.790 --> 34:07.000
[ Grunts ]

34:07.000 --> 34:11.700
[ Breathing heavily ]

34:12.540 --> 34:15.290
[ Police radio chatter ]

34:15.290 --> 34:17.580
Still don't believe
in miracles?

34:17.580 --> 34:21.450
This is everything Adio was
accused of stealing and more.

34:21.450 --> 34:23.580
[ Engine starts ]
How?

34:23.580 --> 34:24.950
Don't want
to talk about it.

34:24.950 --> 34:26.290
Why? 'Cause then
you'd have to admit

34:26.290 --> 34:27.660
something miraculous
is going on here?

34:27.660 --> 34:30.450
Look, there's definitely
something going on,

34:30.450 --> 34:32.700
but even if it isn't just
some series of coincidences,

34:32.700 --> 34:35.830
which it could still be,
there has to be an explanation.

34:35.830 --> 34:36.950
And God's not
good enough for you?

34:36.950 --> 34:38.830
God's a catchall for things
people don't understand.

34:38.830 --> 34:40.580
Any sufficiently
advanced technology

34:40.580 --> 34:42.000
is indistinguishable
from magic.

34:42.000 --> 34:44.410
We just...
need more information.

34:44.410 --> 34:47.620
Right. Technology.
Magic. Gotcha.

34:47.620 --> 34:51.250
Guys, can we go?

34:52.540 --> 35:01.790
♪♪

35:01.790 --> 35:05.450
[ Whispering ]
Jeter retired.

35:05.450 --> 35:06.500
[ Sighs ]

35:06.500 --> 35:10.120
We'll tell him
next season.

35:10.790 --> 35:11.830
Hey,
take it easy, pal.

35:11.830 --> 35:13.620
You don't have to
unpack it all tonight.

35:13.620 --> 35:17.160
I just want to find --
Art!

35:17.160 --> 35:20.120
[ Chuckles ]
There he is.

35:20.120 --> 35:21.250
What else
we got here?

35:21.250 --> 35:24.540
You know, you have your sister
to thank for this.

35:24.540 --> 35:26.580
She saved it all
for you.

35:26.580 --> 35:27.950
Let's see.

35:27.950 --> 35:29.540
[ Sighs ]

35:29.540 --> 35:31.910
[ Objects clattering ]

35:31.910 --> 35:34.290
What's that do?

35:34.290 --> 35:39.330
♪♪

35:39.330 --> 35:40.870
You did this?

35:40.870 --> 35:44.750
You made me feel crazy
for not letting go,

35:44.750 --> 35:48.540
but I was right,
and I'm right this time.

35:48.540 --> 35:53.750
Only this time,you'rethe one
who needs to let go.

35:53.750 --> 36:03.620
♪♪

36:11.040 --> 36:12.790
Hi.

36:12.790 --> 36:15.410
Sorry.
Is now a good time?

36:15.410 --> 36:16.790
Sure.

36:16.790 --> 36:19.160
Jared's at work.

36:19.160 --> 36:22.580
Already knew that.

36:24.950 --> 36:27.750
Want to come in?
No, that's okay.

36:27.750 --> 36:29.160
I have to
be somewhere.

36:29.160 --> 36:33.000
I just wanted to,
um...

36:35.160 --> 36:38.290
I saw
your posts online.

36:38.290 --> 36:40.250
All of them.

36:40.250 --> 36:41.250
Thank you.

36:41.250 --> 36:45.540
You never stopped
being my best friend.

36:45.540 --> 36:49.200
I hope
that doesn't have to change.

36:49.700 --> 36:52.750
Let's play that one by ear,
okay?

36:52.750 --> 36:55.660
Michaela,
I never meant to --

36:55.660 --> 36:57.160
If I'd known
that you were --

36:57.160 --> 37:00.870
What, that I was gonna
come back from the dead?

37:00.870 --> 37:03.200
I'm the one
who's out of place.

37:03.200 --> 37:06.410
You're not.
This isn't on you.

37:06.410 --> 37:09.200
It's okay, Lou.

37:09.200 --> 37:11.620
You love him.

37:11.620 --> 37:14.410
So do you.

37:14.410 --> 37:18.040
But you're the one
he married.

37:18.040 --> 37:21.830
Of course I bless this.
How could I not?

37:23.040 --> 37:25.910
Thank you.

37:26.250 --> 37:30.790
I've -- I've spent
all these years

37:30.790 --> 37:34.290
trying not to feel like
a fraud, you know?

37:34.290 --> 37:38.330
You were the one
he was supposed to marry.

37:38.330 --> 37:40.410
No.

37:40.410 --> 37:41.870
No, after everything
that happened --

37:41.870 --> 37:44.790
the -- the accident, Evie --
it was too intertwined.

37:44.790 --> 37:47.580
There was --
There was too much pain.

37:47.580 --> 37:50.750
I was gonna
give the ring back.

37:50.750 --> 37:55.250
Mick --
I was coming back
to say no.

37:55.250 --> 37:57.450
You're not a fraud.

37:57.450 --> 37:59.250
♪♪

37:59.250 --> 38:01.700
Let it go.

38:01.700 --> 38:03.410
Come here.

38:03.410 --> 38:05.790
[ Sniffles ]

38:05.790 --> 38:06.580
♪♪

38:06.580 --> 38:07.750
Bethany:Yes, we did, people.

38:07.750 --> 38:12.160
Welcome to New York,
where local time is 11:49 p.m.

38:12.160 --> 38:13.330
On behalf of your flight crew,

38:13.330 --> 38:17.540
we'd like to thank you all
for flying Montego Air.

38:17.540 --> 38:19.830
♪♪

38:19.830 --> 38:22.660
[ Cellphone clicks ]

38:26.950 --> 38:29.700
Seriously?
No service?

38:29.700 --> 38:31.330
Same.

38:31.330 --> 38:42.580
♪♪

38:45.750 --> 38:47.410
I'm so sorry.

38:47.410 --> 38:50.080
That wasn't Olive's secret
to tell.

38:50.080 --> 38:51.790
I can't believe
she would --

38:51.790 --> 38:54.540
She did it
for her brother.

38:57.370 --> 39:01.700
Olive is
an amazing young woman.

39:02.540 --> 39:04.370
You've done
an incredible job,

39:04.370 --> 39:08.660
and I can't imagine
how hard that was.

39:08.660 --> 39:11.700
And I don't...

39:14.700 --> 39:19.910
It doesn't matter
where you found the strength

39:19.910 --> 39:22.910
or with whom.

39:28.370 --> 39:31.330
All I wanted
for so long

39:31.330 --> 39:33.500
was to have
you and Cal back,

39:33.500 --> 39:37.410
but it was a want
that hurt so much

39:37.410 --> 39:39.790
that I had to
let it go.

39:39.790 --> 39:42.040
I know.

39:42.040 --> 39:43.790
♪♪

39:43.790 --> 39:46.750
But I never had to.

39:46.750 --> 39:48.830
♪♪

39:48.830 --> 39:52.910
I still love you so damn much,
it hurts.

39:52.910 --> 39:54.830
♪♪

39:54.830 --> 39:59.950
And I know your love for me
is out of practice,

39:59.950 --> 40:03.370
more like a memory...

40:04.200 --> 40:07.290
...but we have
a second chance.

40:07.290 --> 40:10.000
♪♪

40:10.000 --> 40:14.120
Please remember.

40:15.790 --> 40:19.700
[ The Decemberists'
"Once in My Life" plays ]

40:19.700 --> 40:26.540
♪♪

40:26.540 --> 40:28.330
♪ Oh, for once in my ♪

40:28.330 --> 40:32.950
♪ Oh, for once in my life ♪
[ Door closes ]

40:32.950 --> 40:35.580
♪♪

40:35.580 --> 40:38.580
♪ Could just something go ♪

40:38.580 --> 40:43.040
♪ Could just something
go right? ♪

40:43.040 --> 40:46.200
♪♪

40:46.200 --> 40:48.870
♪ Oh, for once in my ♪

40:48.870 --> 40:53.200
♪ Oh, for once in my life ♪

40:53.200 --> 40:56.620
♪♪

40:56.620 --> 41:02.950
♪ I've been waiting
all my life ♪

41:02.950 --> 41:06.450
♪♪

41:06.450 --> 41:13.250
♪ I've been waiting
all my life ♪

41:13.250 --> 41:24.290
♪♪

41:24.290 --> 41:25.500
Kelly:When they let us go,

41:25.500 --> 41:28.000
they told us
we weren't supposed to talk,

41:28.000 --> 41:28.950
but I know my rights.

41:28.950 --> 41:32.870
And now that I've spoken up,
I think they're watching me.

41:32.870 --> 41:37.080
I'm telling you, I think
the government is behind this.

41:37.080 --> 41:40.040
[ Gunshot ]
I mean, if I'm supposed to
own my truth,

41:40.040 --> 41:42.910
don't you think
they should, too?

41:44.700 --> 42:17.120
♪♪
